quran[37]{c,v,t}:
  19,22,"So she conceived him, then she retired with him to a remote place"
  19,23,"Then the birthpangs made her come to the trunk of the palm-tree. She said, \"Oh, would I had died before this and become a thing forgotten, completely forgotten"
  19,24,"Then (one) called out to her from beneath her, \"Do not grieve. Your Lord has already made beneath you a rivulet"
  19,25,"And shake to you the trunk of the palm-tree (and) it will let fall ripe dates down on you, readily reaped"
  19,26,"So eat and drink and comfort your eye, yet in case you ever definitely see any mortal, (Literally: any of the mortals) then say, \"Surely I have vowed fasting to The All-Merciful, so I will never speak today to any human being"
  19,27,"Then she came up with him to her people carrying him. They said, \"O Maryam, (Mary) indeed you have readily come with a fabricated thing"
  19,28,"O sister of Harun, (Aaron) in no way was your father a woeful person, and in no way was your mother a prostitute"
  19,29,"So she pointed to him. They said, \"How shall we speak to one who is (still) in the cradle, a young boy"
  19,30,"He said, \"Surely I am the bondman of Allah. He has brought me the Book and made me a Prophet"
  19,31,"And He has made me blessed wherever I may be, and He has enjoined upon me prayer and Zakat (The poordues) as long as I am alive"
  19,32,"And ever benign to my (female) parent; (Literally: She who gave birt to me) and He has not made me arrogant, wretched"
  19,33,"And peace be upon me, the day I was born, and the day I die, and the day I am made to rise again alive"
  19,34,"That is Isa (Jesus) son of Maryam, in word of truth, concerning which they are wrangling"
  19,35,"In no way is it for Allah to take to Him a child. All Extolment be to Him! When He decrees a Command, then He only says to it, \"Be!\" and it is"
  19,36,"And surely Allah is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him. This is a straight Path"
  19,37,Yet the parties have differed among themselves; so woe to the ones who have disbelieved for the witnessing of a tremendous Day
  19,38,How well they will hear and behold the Day they come up to Us! But the unjust (ones) are today in evident error
  19,39,"And warn them of the Day of regret, as the Command is decreed, and they are in a state of heedlessness, and they do not believe"
  19,40,"Surely, We, Ever We, will inherit the earth and (all) who are upon it, and to Us they will be returned"
  19,41,"And mention in the Book Ibrahim; (Abraham) surely he was most sincere, a Prophet"
  19,42,"As he said to his father, \"O my father, why do you worship that which neither hears nor beholds, nor avails you anything"
  19,43,"O my father, surely there has already come to me (something) of knowledge that did not come up to you; so closely follow me, and I will guide you on a level path"
  19,44,"O my father, do not worship Ash-Shaytan; (The ever-vicious, i.e., the Devil) surely Ash-Shaytan has been most disobedient to The All-Merciful"
  19,45,"O my Father, surely I fear that (some) torment from The All-Merciful will touch you, so that you become a patron to Ash-Shaytan"
  19,46,"Said he, \"Do you desirously shirk from my gods, O Ibrahim? Indeed, in case you do not refrain, indeed I will definitely stone you; so forsake me for a long while"
  19,47,"He said, \"Peace be upon you! I will soon ask my Lord to forgive you; surely He has been Ever-Hospitable to me"
  19,48,"And I keep apart from you and what you invoke apart from Allah; and I will invoke my Lord. It may be that in invoking my Lord, I will not be wretched"
  19,49,"So, as soon as he kept apart from them and what they were worshiping apart from Allah, We bestowed upon him Ishaq and Yaaqub, (Isaac and Jacob, respectively) and each We made a Prophet"
  19,50,"And We bestowed upon them of Our mercy, and We made for them a tongue of sincerity, most exalted"
  19,51,"And mention in the Book Musa; (Moses) surely he was most faithful and he was a Messenger, a Prophet"
  19,52,And We called out to him from the right side of At-Tur (The Mount) and We brought him near in private conference
  19,53,"And We bestowed upon him of Our mercy his brother Har?n, (Aaron) a Prophet"
  19,54,"And mention in the Book Shuaayb; (Ishmael) surely he was sincerely (true) to his promise, and he was a Messenger, a Prophet"
  19,55,And he used to command his family to (keep up) the prayer and (to give) Zakat; (The poordues) and he was most satisfied in the Providence of his Lord
  19,56,"And mention in the Book Idris; surely he was most sincere, a Prophet"
  19,57,And We raised him to a most exalted place
  19,58,"Those are they whom Allah has favored among the Prophets of the offspring of Adam, (Adam) and of the ones We carried with Nuh, (Noah) and of the offspring of Ibrahim (Abraham) and Israel) and of the ones We guided and selected. When the ayat (Verses or signs) of The All-Merciful were recited to them, they collapsed constantly prostrating and weeping. A prostration is to be performed here"